# =====================================================================
# Group 9: fs_context mount-option parser — fs_param_is_* + __fs_parse
# =====================================================================
#
# Linux's modern mount-option parser (fs/fs_parser.c) — fat.ko's
# fs_parameter spec references these as the per-type validators.
# They're DATA in Linux (function pointers stored in a fs_parameter_
# spec table). At module load the loader just patches the relocation
# with the symbol address; no callsite fires here.
#
# We expose all eight as no-op functions. If a future Hamnix mount
# actually parses fat options it would error, but module-load only
# needs the addresses to resolve.

