# was registered in L51. Stubbed because vfat isn't mounted in our
# env — but we route load_nls through the L51 registration table if
# we can find it. For now: return NULL ("no such charset"), which
# the caller handles by falling back to nls_default.
#
# utf16s_to_utf8s converts FAT long-filename UTF-16LE entries into
# UTF-8 for the dcache. Runtime only.

